Call for Papers
2 nd International Workshop on Innovative Internet Information Systems ( IIIS'99 )
focusing on Internet- Based Organizational Memory and Knowledge Management
held in conjunction with the European Conference on Information Systems ( ECIS'99 ) Copenhagen , Denmark
June 21 - 22 , 1999
Organizers = = = = = = = = = = David G . Schwartz Bar- Ilan University , Israel
Monica Divitini & Terje Brasethvik Norwegian University of Science and Technology , Norway
Overview = = = = = = = = The Internet is quickly moving from a marketing tool in which businesses and organization promote sales and awareness , to a core element of any information system architecture . The advent of the Internet as a fundamental infrastructure for the delivery of advanced business information systems has opened up a wide range of questions for the design and development of such systems . The IIIS workshop series deals with different aspects of how the Internet affects and is affected by organizational information systems . This workshop follows the first IIIS workshop held last year in Pisa , Italy .
The theme chose for this year 's workshop is that of Internet-based Organizational Memories and Knowledge Management . Knowledge Management is fast becoming a crucial issue and key factor in the growth of organizations . Managing disparate , heterogeneous knowledge , and making it available in an appropriate manner across the organization is a daunting task . The Internet , intranets , and the World Wide Web have been a significant catalyst in the development of new OM / KM technologies , creating new possibilities and raising new challenges . The workshop aims at discussing the many aspects that are associated both to the development and to the use of OM / KM systems .
This workshop focuses on OM / KM systems that utilize the Internet as their primary architectural base or as a secondary extension to knowledge management systems . This workshop will serve as a forum to present and discuss early results and challenges of innovative Internet-based OM / KM applications .
Aims and Objectives = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = The workshop aims to bring together people with different backgrounds and experiences , providing a forum for the discussion of a wide range of ideas on Innovative Internet Information Systems .
Suggested topics of interest include , but are not limited to :
- Extending legacy corporate and organizational memories to the Internet - Cross-border and multicultural issues for Internet-based OM / KM systems - Knowledge representation , visualization and brokering - Agents for information management - Integrating OM / KM with CMC / communication processes - Organizational memories for cooperation and learning - Case studies of building internet-based OM in enterprises - User involvement in building internet-based OM / KM repositories - Distributed knowledge management
The workshop will last two days and it will take place immediately before ECIS'99 . Selected papers from the Workshop will be considered for publication in the Journal of Internet Research , MCB University Press . http : / / www . mcb . co . uk / cgi-bin / journal 3 / intr
Paper format = = = = = = = = = = = = Authors are invited to submit research contributions representing ongoing or completed work . All papers will be reviewed by the program committee .
Papers should be approximately 5000 words . Formatting guidelines can be found at http : / / www . idi . ntnu . no / ~ monica / iiis- 99 / format . htm
Paper submission = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = Papers can be submitted by e-mail to one of the addresses below . Submissions must be either MS-Word , Postscript or PDF formats ( please , DO NOT compress files ) . Alternatively , initial submission can by done by emailing a URL pointing to an HTML version of the paper .
If , for some reason , you cannot send an electronic copy of your paper , you may submit it as four hard copies to one of the addresses below .
